justification: The fields name, taskType, taskCode, taskDefinitionVersion, taskGroupPriority, firstSubmitTime, submitTime, startTime, endTime, host, executePath, logPath, retryTimes, pid, appLink, duration, maxRetryTimes, retryInterval, workerGroup, environmentCode, environmentConfig, executorId, varPool, executorName, delayTime, taskParams, dryRun, taskGroupId, cpuQuota, and memoryMax are shared across the TaskInstance and TaskInstanceExecuteDto classes. This indicates a strong domain relationship and suggests that these fields represent a concept in the domain that could be encapsulated in its own class.
